.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "April 2025" "v1.0" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
simple_shell \- a basic UNIX command-line interpreter written in C

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./hsh
.RI [ command ]
.br
.B echo "command" | ./hsh

.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B simple_shell
program is a minimal implementation of a command-line shell, capable of executing commands in both interactive and non-interactive modes.

It provides the following features:
.IP \(bu 3
Custom shell prompt
.IP \(bu 3
Command execution using
.B execve
.IP \(bu 3
Support for command arguments
.IP \(bu 3
Searches for executable files using the
.B PATH
environment variable
.IP \(bu 3
Built-in commands:
.B exit
and
.B env
.IP \(bu 3
Graceful handling of
.B EOF
signals (Ctrl+D)

.SH USAGE
.TP
Interactive Mode:
.RS
.nf
$ ./hsh
$ ls
$ /bin/ls -l
$ env
$ exit
.fi
.RE

.TP
Non-Interactive Mode:
.RS
.nf
$ echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh
.fi
.RE

.SH FILES
The following files are part of this shell:
.IP main.c
Entry point and shell loop
.IP execute_command.c
Handles forking and execution of commands
.IP find_command_path.c
Resolves full command paths using PATH
.IP parse_line.c
Parses user input into commands and arguments
.IP shell.h
Header file with function prototypes and constants

.SH AUTHORS
See the AUTHORS file for a list of contributors.

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR sh (1),
.BR bash (1),
.BR execve (2)

.SH BUGS
No known bugs at this time.
